---
title: Events
description: Events provide type-safe communication between modules and external systems. Dispatch events and handle them with full TypeScript support.
---

Events enable type-safe communication within your Directive system. {% .lead %}

---

## Defining Events

Define events in your module schema:

```typescript
const userModule = createModule("user", {
  schema: {
    facts: {
      user: t.object<User>().nullable(),
    },
    events: {
      USER_LOGGED_IN: t.object<{ userId: string; timestamp: number }>(),
      USER_LOGGED_OUT: t.object<{ reason: string }>(),
      PROFILE_UPDATED: t.object<{ field: string; value: unknown }>(),
    },
  },
});
```

---

## Dispatching Events

Dispatch events from resolvers:

```typescript
resolvers: {
  login: {
    requirement: "LOGIN",
    resolve: async (req, ctx) => {
      const user = await auth.login(req.email, req.password);
      ctx.facts.user = user;

      // Dispatch typed event
      ctx.dispatch("USER_LOGGED_IN", {
        userId: user.id,
        timestamp: Date.now(),
      });
    },
  },

  logout: {
    requirement: "LOGOUT",
    resolve: (req, ctx) => {
      ctx.facts.user = null;
      ctx.dispatch("USER_LOGGED_OUT", { reason: req.reason });
    },
  },
}
```

---

## Handling Events

Subscribe to events on the system:

```typescript
const system = createSystem({ module: userModule });

// Handle specific event
system.on("USER_LOGGED_IN", (payload) => {
  console.log(`User ${payload.userId} logged in at ${payload.timestamp}`);
  analytics.track("login", payload);
});

system.on("USER_LOGGED_OUT", (payload) => {
  console.log(`User logged out: ${payload.reason}`);
});
```

---

## Event Handlers in Modules

Define handlers directly in the module:

```typescript
const userModule = createModule("user", {
  schema: {
    events: {
      USER_LOGGED_IN: t.object<{ userId: string }>(),
    },
  },

  handlers: {
    USER_LOGGED_IN: (payload, ctx) => {
      // Access facts
      console.log(`Welcome, ${ctx.facts.user?.name}`);
      // Dispatch more events
      ctx.dispatch("ANALYTICS_TRACK", { event: "login" });
    },
  },
});
```

---

## Cross-Module Events

Events can be shared across modules:

```typescript
// Shared events schema
const sharedEvents = {
  NOTIFICATION: t.object<{ message: string; type: "info" | "error" }>(),
};

const userModule = createModule("user", {
  schema: {
    events: {
      ...sharedEvents,
      USER_LOGGED_IN: t.object<{ userId: string }>(),
    },
  },
  // ...
});

const notificationModule = createModule("notification", {
  schema: {
    events: sharedEvents,
  },

  handlers: {
    NOTIFICATION: (payload, ctx) => {
      showToast(payload.message, payload.type);
    },
  },
});
```

---

## Event Payloads

Events carry typed payloads:

```typescript
schema: {
  events: {
    // Simple payload
    CLICKED: t.object<{ x: number; y: number }>(),

    // Complex payload
    ORDER_PLACED: t.object<{
      orderId: string;
      items: Array<{ id: string; quantity: number }>;
      total: number;
    }>(),

    // No payload
    RESET: t.void(),
  },
}
```

Dispatch with correct types:

```typescript
ctx.dispatch("CLICKED", { x: 100, y: 200 });
ctx.dispatch("ORDER_PLACED", {
  orderId: "123",
  items: [{ id: "abc", quantity: 2 }],
  total: 99.99,
});
ctx.dispatch("RESET"); // No payload needed
```

---

## Unsubscribing

Event subscriptions return an unsubscribe function:

```typescript
const unsubscribe = system.on("USER_LOGGED_IN", (payload) => {
  console.log("Logged in:", payload);
});

// Later: stop listening
unsubscribe();
```

---

## One-Time Handlers

Handle an event only once:

```typescript
system.once("USER_LOGGED_IN", (payload) => {
  // Only runs for the first login
  showWelcomeModal();
});
```

---

## Event History

Access event history (when enabled):

```typescript
const system = createSystem({
  module: userModule,
  debug: { eventHistory: true },
});

// Get all events
const history = system.events.history();

// Filter by type
const logins = system.events.history("USER_LOGGED_IN");
```

---

## Async Handlers

Handlers can be async:

```typescript
handlers: {
  ORDER_PLACED: async (payload, ctx) => {
    await sendConfirmationEmail(payload);
    await updateInventory(payload.items);
  },
}
```

{% callout type="note" title="Async handlers" %}
Async handlers don't block the reconciliation loop. They run fire-and-forget.
{% /callout %}

---

## Events vs Effects

| Events | Effects |
|--------|---------|
| Explicit dispatch | Automatic on fact change |
| Handler-based | Function-based |
| Cross-module communication | Single module scope |
| Named and typed | Implicit triggers |

Use events when you need:
- Explicit communication between modules
- Named, documented interactions
- Decoupled systems

Use effects when:
- Reacting to any fact change
- Side effects within a module
- Simple logging/analytics

---

## Common Patterns

### Audit Trail

```typescript
const auditModule = createModule("audit", {
  schema: {
    facts: {
      logs: t.array(t.object<AuditLog>()),
    },
    events: {
      AUDIT_LOG: t.object<{ action: string; data: unknown }>(),
    },
  },

  handlers: {
    AUDIT_LOG: (payload, ctx) => {
      ctx.facts.logs = [
        ...ctx.facts.logs,
        { ...payload, timestamp: Date.now() },
      ];
    },
  },
});
```

### Error Broadcasting

```typescript
schema: {
  events: {
    ERROR_OCCURRED: t.object<{
      code: string;
      message: string;
      context?: unknown;
    }>(),
  },
}

// In resolver
try {
  await riskyOperation();
} catch (error) {
  ctx.dispatch("ERROR_OCCURRED", {
    code: "OPERATION_FAILED",
    message: error.message,
    context: { operation: "riskyOperation" },
  });
}
```

### State Synchronization

```typescript
handlers: {
  SYNC_REQUESTED: async (payload, ctx) => {
    const serverState = await api.getState();
    ctx.facts.data = serverState;
  },
}
```

---

## TypeScript Integration

Events are fully typed:

```typescript
// Type-safe dispatch
ctx.dispatch("USER_LOGGED_IN", { userId: "123", timestamp: Date.now() });
ctx.dispatch("USER_LOGGED_IN", { wrong: "payload" }); // Type error!

// Type-safe handlers
system.on("USER_LOGGED_IN", (payload) => {
  payload.userId; // string
  payload.timestamp; // number
  payload.wrong; // Type error!
});
```

